NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|OBAR means "Opponents Bid And Raise" which is what happened on this hand. Bergen's theory is, especially when you are short in the opponents suit, you should "pre-balance". |
PG| ***** 44 ***** |


NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|That is, if you make a bid, you are not showing strength particularly, just making a) a lead directing bid if you bid a suit and b) forcing them up. So if Liz had chosen to bid 3@D, that would not be strong, just show nice diamonds.|
PG| ***** 45 ***** |


NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|Doubles in OBAR are still takeout but do not have to show a particularly strong hand, just shortness in the opps suit and 3+-card support in the other suits.|
PG| ***** 46 ***** |


NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|As an OBAR bid, 2N by Liz would be a minor suit takeout double not a strong NT. The theory being that once both of us bid, showing 20 points or so at least, the odds of east having a strong NT are small. And even if East did have a strong NT her partner would not have much. That's how OBAR works. On this hand, given the unfavorable vul, and pretty nice spades, pass is probably best by Jenny.|
PG| ***** 47 ***** |


NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|Now lets look at my hand. Whenever you are 6-4 your hand is much better than its point count. Let me count my Bergen declarer points and see if I have any excuse to try for game.|
PG| ***** 48 ***** |


NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|13 HCP, -1 for dubious @DQ, + 2 length points, +1 for the 6th spade once we find a fit, +1 for the side 4-card heart suit, and +2 points for the singleton gets me to 18.If partner has 8 or so, I want to be in game.|
PG| ***** 49 ***** |


NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|Another thing that many experts play is sometimes called "1-2-3-stop". That means if you play it, is that 3@S by me is not an invite. It simply says that you are expecting the opponents to bid over 2@S and are going to bid 3@S if they do. So you bid 3@S right away as a method of shutting out the opponents bidding.|
PG| ***** 50 ***** |


NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|Had I had fewer points but 6 spades, meaning LOTT says I can bid 3@S with my 9-card fit, and we were playing 1-2-3 stop, I would bid 3@S. |
PG| ***** 51 ***** |


NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|However, on this hand, I bid 3@H which is an invitational bid asking Liz to value heart cards and bid 4@S with nice hearts or just a good 8 or 9. 3@H does not promise 4 hearts, just some points in hearts.|
